Armed robbers shot and killed a man on Saturday night at a petrol station in Archers Post town, Samburu East.The victim was an attendant at the station, said Samburu East sub-county commissioner Johnson Muregi.He was shot while running for his life during the incident at about 7pm.Muregi said witnesses told police the gang of three people had planned to steal money.The suspects believed to be local Morans opened fire but APs responded immediately and launched a pursuit for the criminals.&ldquo;We are working with the community to identify suspects. They will be arrested and charged," he said.The body was taken to a mortuary in Isiolo town.